title: White House at Inch Gow, etc. [A tale.]
author: Pitt, Sarah.
snippet: After that he was going on to Inch Gow,where he was to stay with Mr. Priestley for theremainder of the time. The White House was closedfor the present, given up to the owls and the bats—metaphorically speaking. Even Mrs. Burnett hadforsaken it.
